node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Facts And Science on September 07, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'To eat or not to eat-that is the question. NG MENTALFLOSS.COM What's That Gray Ring You Sometimes See Around Hard-Boiled Hard- Eggs?'.

node.text:
Hard-boiled eggs might be an ideal snack. They’re easy to make, easy to consume, don’t make a mess, and provide protein without an excessive amount of calories.
But if you’ve ever peeled an egg, you might have noticed a possible wrinkle in your plans. Some hard-boiled eggs have a gray or green ring of discoloration between the white and the yolk, which might prompt you to wonder if the chicken in question had some exotic disease or whether the egg is safe to consume. Read more about which types of eggs you should eat  by SWIPING up our post in story.
